title: China donates 9m RMB worth agricultural machinery to Timor-Leste in 2018
description: On February 1st, 2018, the handover ceremony of agricultural equipment from China to Timor-Leste occurred. The ceremony was attended by Chinese Ambassador, Liu Hongyang, and the Timor-Leste Minister of Agriculture. Soon, China attends to provide technical training services to Timor Leste to promote agricultural cooperation. Timor-Leste's Ministry of Agriculture attends to distribute this batch of agricultural machinery and equipment to places with the most urgent need.  These donated equipment include 18 types of equipment such as XCMG excavators and Zoomlion Agricultural Machinery, with a total of 122 units of agricultural equipment and materials worth 9 million yuan. XCMG Group sent a technical service team of 8 people to provide local agricultural machinery operators. For the training, the Ministry of Agriculture of East Timor selected 30 outstanding agricultural machinery operators from all provinces across the country to participate in training.

title: China donates medical supplies to National Hospital of Timor-Leste in 2018 (Linked to #38110)
description: On June 4th, 2018, a ceremony was held for the donation of medical supplies to the Guido Valadares National Hospital of Timor-Leste (东帝汶国立医院). The ceremony was held at the hospital, and Commercial Counsellor Liu Zhenhua and Dean of the National Hospital of Timor-Leste, Anishetto signed the certificate of transfer. As of 2018, China has donated 15 batches of medical equipment worth more than 1,000,000 USD since 2004, see project #38110 for all related medical supplies donation projects.

title: China holds Feed Production and Processing Technology Training Course in Timor-Leste in 2018
description: On August 29th, 2018, the opening ceremony for the 2018 Feed Production and Processing Technology Training Course was held at Timor Leste's Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries. The training course served as a learning opportunity that allowed 50 Timor-Leste students to consult Chinese agricultural experts. The closing ceremony for the bilateral training program was held on September 25th, 2018 at the Longping High-tech Industrial Park.

title: Chinese Embassy in Timor-Leste donates to Office of the First Lady in 2018
description: On March 7, 2018, Chinese Ambassador to Timor-Leste Liu Hongyang and wife of President Francisco Guterres, Cidália Lopes Nobre Mouzinho Guterres, signed a handover certificate for a monetary donation from the Chinese Embassy in Timor-Leste to the Office of the First Lady of Timor-Leste. The donation amount is unknown. The President's Chief of Staff was also present at the signing. The ceremony was held at the Nicolau Lobato Presidential Palace in Dili. The money will be used to support poverty alleviation activities undertaken by the Office of the First Lady.

title: China donates security equipment to Timorese National Police in 2018
description: On March 14, 2018, a ceremony was held at the Timor-Leste National Police Headquarters for the donation of security equipment from China to the Timor-Leste National Police. The donation included multi-functional command and control systems, digital trunking communication systems, explosives removal suits and alcohol testers, and other items. Chinese Ambassador to Timor-Leste, Liu Hongyang, and East Timorese Minister of Defense and Security, Somochu, signed the handover certificate on behalf of the two governments. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.

title: Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs donates vehicle to Timor-Leste Ministry of Foreign Affairs
description: On August 17, 2018, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs donated an official vehicle for use by the Timor-Leste Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation. The handover ceremony was attended by Charge d'affaires of the Chinese Embassy in Timor-Leste Li Fanjie and Timor-Leste Secretary-General Anthony Tuo, among others. The purpose of the donation is to help the Timor-Leste Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation improve office facilities and working conditions. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.

title: China donates ballot boxes to Timor-Leste for Parliamentary Election in 2018
description: On April 23, 2018, the Chinese Ambassador to Timor-Leste, Liu Hongyang, donated 1,000 ballot boxes to the Timor-Leste Government on behalf of China. The ballot boxes were to be used for the early parliamentary elections held on May 12 of that year. Ambassador Liu Hongyang and Timor-Leste Prime Minister Alkatiri attended the donation ceremony, which was held at the Timor-Leste Prime Minister's Office. The monetary value of the donation is unknown.

title: China extends Chinese Government Scholarships to 22 students from Timor-Leste in 2018
description: In 2018, China provided Chinese Government Scholarships for 22 Timorese students. On August 23, 2018, a farewell ceremony for the awarded students was held at the Chinese Embassy in Timor-Leste. The Chinese Government Scholarship provides the support for students from other countries to travel to China and take part in undergraduate, master's, or doctoral programs. title: China sponsors Agricultural Machinery Operation training course for Timor-Leste in 2018
description: On May 7, 2018, a graduation ceremony was held for the 30 Timorese professionals trained in the Agricultural Machinery Equipment Operation and Maintenance Technical Training Course funded by the Chinese government. The graduation ceremony was held in Longping High-tech Industrial Park, Manatuto District, East Timor. The course was reported to have lasted 30 days, indicating that it began in April of 2018. This training was a continuation of China's donation of agricultural machinery to Timor-Leste in February 2018 (see Project ID#63622).
